opic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suicidal Pallies?</span><hr size=1> There's no useful time to use this ability.  It's dumb.<br>
<br>
Suppose you are on a raid with 29 other people.<br>
If you are full health, you don't want to be using this on a main tank, as you can't see what his health is reliably due to lag.  There's just as good a chance you'll kill yourself to heal him when he's at 25% as when he's at 75% or when he's full health.  If the clerics are all OOM, and you have the main tank and yourself still alive, sacrificing yourself for a single complete heal probably isn't going to make or break a fight, meanwhile your continued melee will most certainly help.<br>
<br>
What sucks big time is you can't even use this ability right when you are hurting.  If you could just plainly sacrifice yourself for a cheal, then that would be better.  You could tank for a while in a bad situation, and your last dying effort is your sacrifice of health.  As it is now, if you use this when you are almost dead, don't you just heal a crap amount on another person?<br>
<br>
Then again, this is still better than the Mass Group Buff that mages get.  :) <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Shaman of one race or another
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukormur21.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kormur21</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 3:25:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11334.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Acts of Valor</span><hr size=1> This would not be my 1st class skill I get but it is still a good ability.  LoH(Lay on Hands) is one of the best taunt in the game, it is a instant heal that heals the person for around the base hp of the paladin naked.(But there is a aa skill that make LoH into a complete heal)  <br>
<br>
What I like to do on big fights is heal the MT(Main Tank) with superior heals so the clerics will have a little more time to do the CH rotation.  But if I start to see the CH fail then I LoH the MT, doing this will probably make the mob attack me if the MT health is too low.  That is where DA(Divine Aura) comes in but is pretty hard to get off when the mob is attacking me.  <br>
<br>
Once the CH rotation is looking good then I start attacking the mob, I also have a assist button to assist off the mob.  When I am attacking the mob I can't see the hp of the MT but I check on him now and then.  The MT will usually be a warrior and I look to see if he goes berzerk, when he goes berzerk then something is wrong.  That is when LoH or Acts of Valor can save the MT and keep the CH rotation going.  Killing the paladin but hopefully the goal is achieve.<br>
<br>
-Kormur Flint <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umcx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 5:28:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11334.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Acts of Valor</span><hr size=1> I love the RP aspect of this skill, however, as pointed out, it isnt designed well.<br>
<br>
Points are far to few and precious for me currently to even consider this skill anyways, and I would put improved LH far ahead of it in desireablitly(altho I allways thought CHeal LH should be a lvl 60 upgrade).<br>
<br>
With all of the other skills avail to a paladin, and the poor design of this particular skill, i dont expect many if any pallies have it yet.<br>
<br>
McBash <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usondorvalorike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sondor Valorike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 7:01:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11334.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   My thoughts...</span><hr size=1> I think it would be more useful as a fleeting regeneration at like 200hp a tick, something like celestial healing. Then no matter what the persons health is at the time you smack em, they most likely will get the full effect of you killing yourself. As is....SCREW that shyite mo fo. Like Juujuu said it's pretty much currently useless, and unless i was level 60 with every other point maxed out, i'd never waste my time getting points for this crap.<br>
