<br>
Endgame fights are not won anymore because one person can perform an instant heal that no one had planned.  They're won now because 100% of the healing is planned ahead of time.  Sure, every few fights I probably end up saving a tank for another minute with it, but in situations where we're actually going to win, LoH rarely if ever needs to be used.<br>
<br>
There was a time when I held it as a point of pride that I never used the ability on myself on raids.  Now, I pretty much use it on myself exclusively, as a way of making sure clerics don't have to spend time worrying about me when they have better things to do.<br>
<br>
Given that I don't get a lot of use out of LoH, I really don't see the point in getting AoV right now, even though for a YEAR before Luclin came out, I was publically begging for that _exact_ ability to be added to the game.  Back then, LoH was really important to my raids.  But now I feel differently, because the game has changed much.<br>
<br>
I have the points saved up that I could log in right now and get AoV, but I don't intend to.<br>
<br>
